cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.DM 

The paper focuses on the performance analysis of randomised search heuristics, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of optimization and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with the analysis of algorithms and functions, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper presents analytical results and experiments, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
